comment:
* Represents a query that contains information required for StatsManager to return relevant metric
 * data.
 *
 * @hide

variables.name: DIALECT_SQLITE
variables.comment: * Query passed is of SQLite dialect.

methods.name: public int getSqlDialect()
methods.comment: * Returns the SQL dialect of the query.

methods.name: public String getRawSql()
methods.comment: * Returns the raw SQL of the query.

methods.name: public int getMinSqlClientVersion()
methods.comment: * Returns the minimum SQL client library version required to execute the query.

methods.name: public byte[] getPolicyConfig()
methods.comment:
* Returns the wire-encoded StatsPolicyConfig proto that contains information to verify the
     * query against a policy defined on the underlying data. Returns null if no policy was set.
